== Pesto ==

Cut the @echalion shallot{2} in half through the root, peel and then finely chop into ½cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, then cut in half lengthways. Cut each half into four strips lengthways, then chop the strips into 1cm cubes.

Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into 1cm cubes.

Finely chop the @basil{1}(finely chopped) and half the @wild rocket{1}(roughly chopped).

> Tip: Don't worry, there may be a lot of prep, but it's all plain sailing from here!

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil!) and add the @pine nuts{40%g}. Dry-fry for ~{1%minute}, or until they start to turn golden.

> Tip: Watch them like a hawk or they will burn!

Once golden, tip your pine nuts onto your #chopping board{} and chop them as finely as you can (don't wash the pan, you'll use it later to dry-fry the courgette!).

Put your basil, chopped rocket and pine nuts in a #bowl{}. Sprinkle in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and pour in your best quality @olive oil{6%tbsp}.

Add a quarter of your garlic and mix everything together thoroughly, this is your pesto.

> Tip: If you have a #food processor{}, you can use it here, but we prefer the satisfaction of doing it by hand!

== Tomato Salad ==

For your tomato salad, squeeze the @lemon{1/2}(juiced) into another bowl and pour in a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Add your tomato and a quarter of your shallot and mix everything together.

== Orzo ==

Put your remaining shallot in a #saucepan{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} on medium heat and cook for ~{3-4%minutes}, then add the rest of your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @orzo{180%g} and stir it around until it is nicely coated, then pour in the @water{400%ml} and add the @vegetable stock pot{1}.

Bring to the boil, then turn the heat down and simmer for ~{10%minutes} or until your pasta is 'al dente' and the liquid has been absorbed.

> Tip: 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle. Stir from time to time to ensure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan!

> Tip: If all the liquid has been absorbed and the pasta is not quite cooked, just add a little more water and keep cooking.

== Courgettes ==

While your pasta is cooking, put the pan you used for your pine nuts back on medium heat without any oil.

Once the pan is hot, add your courgette and cook for ~{7-8%minutes} until charred, turning occasionally.

Once charred, remove the pan from the heat.

> Tip: If they are not very charred, just leave them cooking for a bit longer.

== To Serve ==

Once your pasta is cooked, stir through three-quarters of your pesto along with your courgette.

Serve in #bowls{} with the rest of your rocket, tomato salad and a spoonful of remaining pesto on top.